2022 Jinen Kai Dan Test 🥋

It feels so good to put on my do-gi again! 🥰 I recently finished an intensive 13 weeks of working a full-time clinical rotation while taking classes. To say the least, it has been challenging mentally and physically. Shortly after, I was simultaneous prepping for this Dan test and my final examinations. Life is about rising to the challenge, and overcoming our self-doubt and hesitation. Thank you Sensei for nominating me to test for my next degree, and pushing me to my best potential. Some small clips from the testing 😊🙏🏻

T-2 days.

#teamtrials #usakarate

North American Cup🥉

It’s good to be back on the tatami! Although the result is not what I would’ve hoped for, I trust in God’s timing and I’ll lay my dreams in His capable hands. 

I’m working hard towards my last few weeks of my last clinical rotation of PT school! I’ve had amazing learning opportunities in inpatient acute care experience, working the trauma floor, emergency department, surgical intensive care unit, and the burn care unit. Our profession is so inspiring! 🧠

35 days til graduation on May 12th, and 48 days til Senior PKF championships on May 25th. 

I’ll finish my DPT program strong and be back even stronger for Continentals 👊🏻

Thank you for all the congratulation messages, and for the messages saying “it’s good to see you back!” I’ve greatly missed representing my country and cheering my teammates on. 

Thank you to God for helping me stay mentally strong and faithful through the process, to my family and friends for their endless encouragement, my Jinen Kai family and my Kenseikan family for all the training and support, @javiermantilla3028 and the Team USA coaches for their guidance, and to @catalystptandwellness for keeping me feeling good! 

I’ll keep forging forward to be the best version of myself both on and off the tatami 🙇🏻‍♀️

#teamusa #usakarate #kata #papuren

Reintroducing, Dr. Jessica May Kwong of Physical Therapy✌️❤️💛

Three years have flown by so quickly, and I have made it to the finish line! Thank you to God for filling me with this dream and providing me the physical and mental strength to complete this program. 

I’m filled with so much gratitude for my family and my friends for supporting my dreams, being there for me with positive words of comfort, reassuring hugs, and lending a shoulder to cry on when I was struggling. This DPT program pushed me far beyond my comfort zone to grow into my full potential as a future physical therapist. This journey was full of sacrifices and hard work to balance my role as a USA Karate athlete and a full time student in this doctoral program. 

I found amazing lifelong friends among my classmates, people that I was able to grow alongside as we challenged ourselves to the fullest. I could not have made it to the end if it wasn’t for my core ladies. I’m so beyond excited to see what the future holds for all of us. 

The first of a few graduation posts to come in the near future. But for now, I’m signing off with a few more letters after my name. Keeping fighting on my fellow Trojans! ✌️❤️💛

Yours truly, 

Jessica Kwong DPT 🎓

A la final! 🙌

Everything is in God’s timing. I’m beyond excited for my first Senior PKF kata finals tonight! Thank you for all the congratulations and good luck messages you’ve sent me so far. Your energy is powering me til the end 🙏🏻 Recharging for the final round on the tatami tonight, I’ll give it my all!! 👊🏻 

#usakarate #teamusa #kata #karate #hirota #papuren

Pan American Silver Medalist 🥈 

What a month it’s been! From getting my doctorate degree last week, to making it to my first senior pkf finals and earning silver this week. All I can say is that God’s timing is perfect, and that He will always provide. When I asked God to help me gain confidence in myself, He gifted me an opportunity to grow into it. 

While the performance was not a full representation of what I can do, I strongly believe it was a great first step towards what I am envisioning for myself. I will be training hard to make more finals in the years to come! 

Thank you again to my family and friends for their never ending support. I am able to keep pushing because I have my village with me every step of the way. Thank you to @lesstalkmorekarate for the kata training and mental support throughout my trip, to @kenseikandojo for the kata adjustments leading up, and @javiermantilla3028 for keeping me primed and focused for each round. Thank you everyone for your prayers, positive energy, and good luck messages. Each one fueled me in this finals match! I’ll continue to keep striving to be a better version of myself each time I step onto the tatami. 

I am so proud to stand alongside my fellow USA kata teammates knowing we made PKF history with an all USA kata finals 🇺🇸 

Time to head back home to rest and analyze for the next step in the journey. This is just the beginning! 🙌

#USAKARATE #TEAMUSA #PKFKarate2023 #WKF #Kata #justthebeginning

Karate1 Series A Larnaca 🇨🇾 

15th place

Round 1 ✅ 
Round 2 ✅ 
Semifinals ❌

It’s been 3 years and 7 months since my last Karate1 event. It felt so good to return to the tatami on this stage. Although my body didn’t respond how I would’ve liked, I’m grateful for God carrying me to the semifinals round. Time to analyze, and train hard for the next! I’ll keep working hard to bring an improved version of myself to the next stage. 🙏🏻

This tournament is also dedicated to my grandmother, who recently passed. She would always give me a phone call before I flew. She’d tell me she’s praying for me, and to believe and have no fear, because God was on my side. Although I would’ve like to have bring back a better result, I know she would be proud just the same. Love you and miss you 婆婆. 🤍🕊️

Thank you to everyone who has been sending me good energy, support, and love, I truly appreciate it! To my family, friends, dojo family, thank you for everything. I wouldn’t be here without my village 🙏🏻🤍

And that’s a wrap for the 2023 competition season 🥋

Although the season did not end as well as I had hoped, finishing 41st out of 112 athletes in Series A Matosinhos, there was a lot of good that came out of 2023. I was able to accomplish one of my biggest goals for this year, which was to make the Senior PKF finals, marking my best finish in Senior continentals. This past Series A has given me a fresh perspective of how to approach my training and my kata performance, which I really look forward to working on and refining for 2024. I’m excited to get back to training to show an improved version of myself at Senior Team USA trials 🇺🇸 

Thank you so much to my family, friends, Sensei and Jinen Kai family for all being a part of my village that provides me with so much support. I’m able to keep pushing with your help. 🙏🏻 A big thank you to @chargelusa for providing me the energy and nutrients to fuel my training 👊

And a very special thank you to @rey.chinen for this trip! It has been so motivating to watch you, and I’m so grateful for our Karate talks 🙏🏻 

As the year comes to a close, I reflect on the passion for Karate that God has placed in my heart. I know He will continue to provide, and that everything is in His perfect timing. Thank you all for your support and energy, God bless! 🤍🙏🏻

Goodbye 2023, Hello 2024 ☀️

Reflecting on 2023, it was filled with both highs and lows. I finished my doctorate physical therapy program, and achieved my Karate goal of making the finals in the Pan American Championships. But also this year, I lost my grandmother. With great loss, I am learning to navigate the changes within myself and my family; and it has also shaped how I want to approach the new year. 

I’m ready to push to further heights in all aspects in 2024. Continuing to pursue growth and happiness, to refining current passions and chasing new ones 🙏🏻 Thank you so much to my family, my friends, and my Jinen Kai dojo family for supporting me throughout my personal, professional, and Karate journey. 

Let’s live each day to the fullest with positivity and gratitude!!! And let’s work hard to overcome our obstacles as they come, and to push towards our dreams in 2024!!! I am also here to cheer you on in your endeavors 😊🫶🙌

Thank you all for being a part of my life journey, supporting me and sending me positivity and love. I truly appreciate each and every one of you!!! Let’s be our kindest, happiest, and healthiest version of ourselves in 2024 🥹🙏🏻🫶
